snippet: Tiger Woods said he fought his swing, which he had been working on for more than a year, and finished his round at the Wells Fargo Championship with a one-over-par 73.
abstract: Poor performance by Tiger Woods causes him to miss the cut at the Wells Fargo Championship golf tournament. (M)2
lead_paragraph: CHARLOTTE, N.C. -- Wandering drives and errant putts undermined Tiger Woods on Friday at the Wells Fargo Championship, as he missed the cut for the eighth time in 267 P.G.A. events and for the second time in a row at this tournament. Woods had never missed the cut at the same event more than once as a pro until Friday when he failed to take advantage of a course that allowed low scores in the morning session, when he played.
